y have lower star\nforming rates than the off-nuclear regions despite the presence of abundant\ndense gas and dust, suggesting that the latter is a necessary but not\nsufficient condition for on-going star formation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 10 Jun 2004 20:35:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
